article_title: Obamacare's Dull Enrollment Trends Mask Its Political Triumph

article_metadata.description: Even as ObamaCare stumbles, it doesn’t follow that the program crumbles. It is narrowing into an entitlement largely for for what the Census Bureau defines as the “working class” -- lower middle-class families who earn too much to qualify for Medicaid, but instead fall into the sweet spot of ObamaCare’s subsidies, getting enough financial support to make the program’s overpriced plans affordable.
article_metadata.author: Scott Gottlieb
